<p><b>What is a top-down design structure?</b> Top-Down Approach. In the top-down design approach, the whole system is successively partitioned into a hierarchy of subsystems. On the top level a behavioral description is used. This description is partitioned into a structural description with behavioral descriptions of the components.</p>
